cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.CE

The paper proposes a new approach to capturing game context in professional ice hockey using Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) and machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SD (Software Development). The paper also involves modeling player performance, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
